On **.NET 10 SDK**, you get native MTP support via `global.json` — no `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` needed. That property is only for .NET 9 and earlier.

Add a `test` section to your `global.json`:

```json
{
  "sdk": {
    "version": "10.0.100"
  },
  "test": {
    "runner": "Microsoft.Testing.Platform"
  }
}
```

**Key differences from .NET 9 setup:**

| .NET 9 and earlier | .NET 10+ |
|---|---|
| `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` in Directory.Build.props | `"test": { "runner": "Microsoft.Testing.Platform" }` in global.json |
| Must use `--` separator: `dotnet test -- --report-trx` | Arguments passed directly: `dotnet test --report-trx` |

So on .NET 10 you can **remove** `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` from your props files entirely and drop the `--` separator from your CLI invocations.

You still need the framework-specific runner enablement (`EnableMSTestRunner`, `EnableNUnitRunner`, etc.) and `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` — those are unchanged.
